# SplitDisk — Approved cryptographic dependencies

Do not substitute, fork, or vendor crypto crates except for security advisories with review.

Use README.md **Section 4.4** table and **Section 16** `Cargo.toml` list. Core crypto includes: `chacha20poly1305`, `serpent`, `twofish`, `poly1305`, `p384`, `hkdf`, `blake3`, `argon2`, `vsss-rs`, `reed-solomon-erasure`, `zeroize`, `subtle`; optional `sequoia-openpgp`; optional `pqcrypto-frodo` (FrodoKEM-1344, feature-gated).

Non-crypto: `ratatui`, `nix`, `rusb`, `gpt`, `fatfs`, `cpio`, `flate2` per image builder needs (README 16).

Adding any new crypto crate requires audit review and README update.
